{"id":"smoke-5fi","title":"Zustand State Stores: Session, Canvas, Grid","description":"Set up the Zustand state stores that drive the entire renderer UI. We use Zustand because it is minimal, fast, selector-based (avoids re-renders), and works well with refs for performance-critical paths.

## What to Build

### src/renderer/stores/sessionStore.ts

```typescript
interface Session {
  id: string;                    // uuid
  title: string;                 // user-editable or auto from CWD basename
  cwd: string;                   // working directory
  position: { x: number; y: number };  // canvas position (grid-aligned)
  size: { cols: number; rows: number; width: number; height: number };
  zIndex: number;
  status: 'running' | 'exited';
  exitCode?: number;
  createdAt: number;
}

interface SessionStore {
  sessions: Map<string, Session>;
  focusedId: string | null;
  highlightedId: string | null;     // sidebar hover highlight
  nextZIndex: number;

  createSession: (cwd: string, position?: { x: number; y: number }) => Session;
  removeSession: (id: string) => void;
  updateSession: (id: string, patch: Partial<Session>) => void;
  focusSession: (id: string) => void;
  highlightSession: (id: string | null) => void;
  bringToFront: (id: string) => void;  // increments nextZIndex, assigns to session
}
```

Use Map<string, Session> internally but expose array selectors for React list rendering. Keep immutable updates simple with spread operators (no immer needed initially).

### src/renderer/stores/canvasStore.ts

```typescript
interface CanvasStore {
  panX: number;
  panY: number;
  zoom: number;              // 0.1 to 3.0
  gridSize: number;          // default 20px

  setPan: (x: number, y: number) => void;
  setZoom: (zoom: number) => void;
  setGridSize: (size: number) => void;
}
```

IMPORTANT: These store values are NOT used for rendering the CSS transform during active pan/zoom. That is done via React.useRef for performance. The store values are synced periodically (on drag-end, zoom-end) for persistence and sidebar pan-to features.

### src/renderer/stores/gridStore.ts

```typescript
interface GridStore {
  gridSize: number;           // pixels per grid cell (default 20)
  snapEnabled: boolean;       // toggle snapping
  showGrid: boolean;          // toggle grid visibility

  setGridSize: (size: number) => void;
  toggleSnap: () => void;
  toggleGrid: () => void;
  snapToGrid: (value: number) => number;  // Math.round(value / gridSize) * gridSize
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- Stores can be imported and used in React components
- sessionStore.createSession() creates a session with a UUID, default size (80x24, 640x480), and returns it
- canvasStore.setPan/setZoom update values readable via selectors
- gridStore.snapToGrid(107) with gridSize=20 returns 100
- gridStore.snapToGrid(113) with gridSize=20 returns 120
- Selectors using useStore(store, selector) only re-render when selected value changes
- Session Map supports efficient lookup by ID","status":"open","priority":0,"issue_type":"feature","owner":"chanjun.park@wisetechglobal.com","created_at":"2026-03-14T13:16:45Z","created_by":"marlboro-red","updated_at":"2026-03-14T13:16:45Z"}

{"id":"smoke-6mw","title":"Performance Optimization: Viewport Culling, Thumbnails, WebGL Management","description":"Implement viewport culling (only render terminals visible in viewport) and thumbnail mode (replace terminals with lightweight placeholders when zoomed out). These are the key optimizations that make Smoke scale to 20+ terminals.

## What to Build

### src/renderer/canvas/useViewportCulling.ts

Returns a Set<string> of session IDs currently visible in viewport:

```typescript
function isVisible(session, pan, zoom, canvasRect, margin = 200) {
  const vpLeft = -pan.x / zoom;
  const vpTop = -pan.y / zoom;
  const vpRight = vpLeft + canvasRect.width / zoom;
  const vpBottom = vpTop + canvasRect.height / zoom;

  return (
    session.position.x + session.size.width >= vpLeft - margin &&
    session.position.x <= vpRight + margin &&
    session.position.y + session.size.height >= vpTop - margin &&
    session.position.y <= vpBottom + margin
  );
}
```

Recalculation triggers:
- On pan-end (debounced 100ms)
- On zoom-end (debounced 100ms)
- On session create/delete/move
- NOT on every frame during active pan/zoom (defeats purpose of using refs)

200px margin prevents visible pop-in at viewport edges during fast pan.

### Applying Culling in Canvas.tsx

```tsx
{sessions.map(session => {
  if (!visibleIds.has(session.id)) return null;
  const isThumbnail = zoomRef.current < THUMBNAIL_THRESHOLD; // 0.4
  return isThumbnail
    ? <TerminalThumbnail key={session.id} session={session} />
    : <TerminalWindow key={session.id} session={session} zoom={zoom} />;
})}
```

### src/renderer/terminal/TerminalThumbnail.tsx

Lightweight placeholder when zoom < 0.4:
- Same position/size as terminal window
- Shows: status dot, session title, last 5 lines of terminal output as static text
- NO xterm.js instance mounted (critical for WebGL context limits)
- Minimal DOM: just a div with styled text

### Terminal Text Snapshot

Before switching to thumbnail mode, capture last N lines:

```typescript
const getSnapshot = () => {
  const buffer = terminal.buffer.active;
  const lines: string[] = [];
  const startRow = Math.max(0, buffer.cursorY - 5);
  for (let i = startRow; i <= buffer.cursorY; i++) {
    lines.push(buffer.getLine(i)?.translateToString() || '');
  }
  return lines;
};
```

### WebGL Context Management

Browsers cap active WebGL contexts at ~8-16. Strategy:
1. Viewport culling ensures only visible terminals have WebGL
2. Thumbnail mode at zoom < 0.4 removes xterm entirely
3. When terminal goes off-screen: do NOT dispose xterm (keeps scrollback). Instead unmount DOM but keep Terminal instance in memory.
4. When terminal returns to view: re-attach with terminal.open(container)
5. If off-screen > 60 seconds: dispose WebGL addon to free GPU. Re-create on return.

### Detach/Reattach Pattern

```typescript
// Detach (off-screen): remove DOM but keep Terminal alive
if (!isVisible && terminal.element) {
  terminal.element = null; // or similar detach
}

// Reattach (back in view):
if (isVisible && containerRef.current && !terminal.element) {
  terminal.open(containerRef.current);
  // Re-load WebGL addon if it was disposed
}
```

## Acceptance Criteria
- Terminals outside viewport NOT rendered in DOM (verify in DevTools Elements)
- Fast pan does not cause visible pop-in (200px margin)
- At zoom < 0.4, terminals switch to thumbnail mode
- Thumbnails show title, status, and text preview
- Zooming back in restores full terminal with scrollback intact
- 20+ sessions without frame drops during pan/zoom
- WebGL context count stays manageable (check document.querySelectorAll('canvas').length)
- Memory usage stable with off-screen terminals (no unbounded growth)
- Transition between thumbnail and full mode is smooth (no flash/flicker)","status":"open","priority":1,"issue_type":"task","owner":"chanjun.park@wisetechglobal.com","created_at":"2026-03-14T13:20:34Z","created_by":"marlboro-red","updated_at":"2026-03-14T13:20:34Z"}

